Scientists have found an animal that can live 500 years.
The international group of biologists came to the conclusion that the most long-lived vertebral animal is the Greenland polar sharp, which can live about 500 years.
Scientists conducted a radio-carbon analysis of the crystal of the eye of 28 Greenland sharks.
The biggest sharp, the length of which exceeds five meters, can be from 272 to 512 years old.
Biologists believe that an important role in the longevity of the sharks plays low metabolism, which leads to slow development.
The females of Greenland sharks reach sexual maturity only at the age of 150.
It was previously believed that the longest of all spinal animals lives the " neighbor" of the sharks - the Greenland whale.
The oldest person known by scientists was a little over 210 years old.
