Head of the administration of the President of the Russian Federation Anton Weino.
On Friday, August 12, Vladimir Putin appointed Anton Weino as the head of the administration of the President of Russia.
This post was previously held by Sergey Ivanov.
“The head of the state by his decree appointed Anton Weino as the head of the administration of the President of the Russian Federation, releasing him from the occupied position,” the decree, signed by Putin and published on the site of the Kremlin said.
Since May 2012, Weino has been the Deputy Head of the Administration of the President of the Russian Federation.
Anton Eduardovich Weino was born on February 17, 1972 in Tallinn.
Father - Edward Weino, Chairman of the Business Council of Cuba-Russia in the Chamber of Commerce and Industry of the Russian Federation and Vice-President on Foreign Relations and Interaction with Shareholders of AutovAZ.
Carl Weino was from 1978 to 1988 the first secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Estonia.
In 1996 he graduated from the Moscow State Institute of International Relations of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Russia, the Faculty of International Relations.
From 1996 to 2001 he worked at the Russian Embassy in Japan, then at the Second Department of Asia of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Russia.
From 2002 to 2004 he held various positions in the Office of the Protocol of the President of the Russian Federation.
From 2004 to 2007 - Deputy Chief Protocol and Organizational Administration of the President of the Russian Federation.
From 2007 to 2007 he was the first deputy director of the Protocol of the President of the Russian Federation.
From October 2007 to April 2008 - Deputy Head of the Apparatus of the Government of the Russian Federation.
On 25 April 2008, he was appointed the head of the protocol of the President of the Government of the Russian Federation, the Deputy Head of the Apparatus of the Government of the Russian Federation.
From December 27, 2011 - Minister of the Russian Federation - Head of the Apparate of the Government of the Russian Federation.
On May 22, 2012 he was appointed Deputy Head of the Administration of the President of the Russian Federation.
He is free to speak English and Japanese languages.
Valid state counselor of the Russian Federation of Class 1 (class rule assigned by the Decree of the President of the Russian Federation of January 22, 2008).
Honorary Charter of the President of the Russian Federation (February 16, 2012) for the merits in ensuring the activities of the Government of the Russian Federation and many years of good faith work.
