On the pension market started the largest deal M&A - "KIT Finance Pension Administrator" launched the process of uniting four under-controlled NPFs.
As a result, on the basis of the "Gazfond Pension Acquisitions" will be created a NPF with a volume of accumulations of about 373 billion rubles.
About the launch of the procedure of unification of four pension funds - "KIT Finance", "Promagrofond", "Heritage" and "Gazfond Pension Acquisitions" - yesterday announced the owner of 100% funds LLC "KIT Finance Pension Administrator".
“Reorganization is carried out in agreement with the Central Bank in compliance with the requirements of non-aggravation of the conditions of existing contracts,” the company said in a statement.
The unification is carried out on the basis of "Gazfond Pension Acquisitions".
As noted by the Director-General of this NPF Oleg Bialoshitsky, the association of funds allows to solve several tasks: expansion of the geography of presence, concentration of resources for development, reduction of costs, tirage of best practices of each of the funds and optimization of corporate management.
According to him, the indicative deadline for the completion of the consolidation is the second quarter of 2017.
As a result of the unification of the NPF "Gazfond Pensions" will become the largest player on the OPS market.
According to data on March 31, the amount of pension accumulations of the united funds exceeded 373 billion rubles.
As follows from the report on the site of the funds, the beneficiaries of their owner - "KIT Finance Pension Administrator" - are currently Anatoly Gavrilenko (through the controlled LLC owns 65%) and NPF "Gazfond" (35%).
However, the group itself launched much later than the competitors.
So, the control group O1 NPF "Future" absorbed the "Stalfond" earlier this year.
Currently, this unified NPF joins the Urasib and the Russian Standard funds.
"Uniting into a single structure, in addition to reducing costs, is necessary to solve structural tasks," said Nikolai Sidorov, the Director-General of the NPF "Future".
Active work on the consolidation of funds from April is going and in the pension group "Safmar" - the NPF "European", "Education and Science" and "Regional Fund" should join the NPF "Safmar" until the end of the current year.
In 2017 they will be joined by the NPF Trust.
"The unification of the funds will give the effect of strengthening the control of risks, operational processes and expenses," Saffmar said in a statement.
The break in the unification of funds, which "KIT Finance Pension Administrator" has suffered, can be caused by several reasons, experts say.
Until recently, the NPF could not buy more than 40% of the volume of the output of infrastructure bonds in which the group was actively placed.
After the amendments to the decision of the Central Bank in March of this year on a number of issuers that meet the requirements of the regulator, such restrictions no longer exist.
If necessary, the entire release can be purchased by one major player," says Yuri Nogin, director of the rating group of the ACRA financial institutions.
Several NPF leaders from the top-15 on assets another possible reason for the break call the division of influence spheres and, as a result, personnel appointments in a single fund, which had to be agreed by the group owners.
Yesterday, Anatoly Gavrilenko was unavailable for comments.
The request "Ъ" to the NPF "Gazfond" was also not answered.
Although the consolidation of funds is a hard-working and untouched event, on a long distance this decision will be justified.
As the general director of the consulting company "Pension Partner" Sergey Okolesnov notes, "Gazfond Pension Accumulations" has less flow, the accession will allow to stabilize the base of other funds of the group.
At the same time, a more successful experience of KIT Finance and Promagrofund will be required in building retail sales of OPS, as well as the use of more modern software.
The demand of the central bank to the processes and staff of the NPF is constantly growing, so duplicating the infrastructure on four funds with a single investment policy is unlikely, says Executive Director for corporate ratings "Expert RA" Pavel Mitrofanov.
“The effect of the reduction of the duplicating functions will uncertainly cross possible unification costs,” Mr. Mitrofanov notes.
The costs for the unification of the four funds Sergey Okolesnov estimates in 30-50 million rubles.
“The expenditure for the maintenance of four funds of such sizes is about 400 million rubles per year, with the consolidation in the medium-term perspective the budget will actually cut twice,” Mr. Okolesnov said.
