Bulgaria shows inflation for the first time in eight months
Inflation in Bulgaria was 1% per month in July, according to national statistics.
This is the highest in the years (from June 2012) and the first above zero since October last year, when positive 0.2% were shown.
The average annual inflation, measured by the IPC, in the last 12 months (August 2015 - July 2016) compared to the previous 12 months (August 2014 - July 2015) was -0,8%.
The index of consumer prices in July 2016 compared to June 2016 was 101,0%, that is, the monthly inflation was 1,0%.
The inflation index since the beginning of the year (July 2016 compared to December 2015) was -0.2%, and the annual inflation in July 2016 compared to July 2015 was -0.2%.
In July 2016, compared to the previous month, a price increase was observed for the following consumer goods groups: food and non-alcoholic beverages (1,7 %); transportation (1,8 %); leisure and culture (6,3 %); restaurants and hotels (1,2 %); other goods and services (0,3 %).
Prices have decreased for clothing and shoes (2,2 %); furniture, household equipment and regular maintenance (0,5 %); health (0,1 %).
The prices remained at the same level as in the previous month for alcoholic beverages and tobacco; housing conditions, water, electricity, gas and other types of fuel; communication systems; and education.
