Notifications on transport tax will cease to be sent by mail - www.zr.ru
The tax inspection has changed the procedure for sending notifications on property taxes.
All Russian car owners are accustomed to the unchanged scheme for years: in the summer and autumn they receive by mail a ticket to pay the transport tax for the previous year.
However, many of them will not be expected this year.
The fact is that tax inspection without excessive noise has changed the procedure for informing citizens.
Those registered in the "Personal Office of the taxpayer" on the official website of the agency nalog.ru, notifications will come in electronic form.
In the inspection, such Russians were automatically identified as online users and pulled them out of the standard, “paper” mail.
The news will affect all vehicle and real estate owners.
The rest will still receive usual letters.
However, the possibility to return to the old scheme is also available to the owners of the account on the site.
For this, they will have to visit the tax department during August and write a statement.
On the one hand, the new order is more modern and convenient.
The notification will appear in the "personal office" immediately after preparation, while the letter will last for a few days and may be completely lost.
Additionally, the number of users of the internet service of tax inspection exceeded 18 million people, which will allow the department to seriously save on the mail.
On the other hand, the modest news on the website of the inspection is clearly not enough to inform citizens of the changed procedure.
Some could register in the "personal office" to get one-time service and for a long time forgot about it.
These people will not wait for notifications by mail and, without knowing it, will fall into the category of non-payers with all the consequences.
Access to the "Personal Office of the taxpayer" is made in three ways: through the account of the portal gosuslugi.ru, using an electronic signature or entering the login and password indicated in the registration card.
The latter can be obtained personally at any tax inspection department ( regardless of the place of registration).
The tax must be paid by 1 December this year.
The notification began in July.
